RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 22000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD OR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs. If no three-year-olds are entered, older weight wi ll revert to 122lbs.

CLAIM.OWNER: Mary E. Eppler Racing Stable, Inc.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ BIZNESS stalked along the inside, tipped out under rousing midway around the turn and took aim from the five path at the top of the lane, bid passing the eighth pole, took the lead, and drew clear in the final sixteenth. UPSTREET pressed in the four path, took over the lead from the three path midway around the turn and was cued right handed into the stretch, kept on but was caught by the outer eventual winner just past the eighth pole to finish with place. EXTRA INDY tracked in the four path, was under a ride in the five path rounding the turn and fanned out to the eight path into the stretch, and was up for show. FINAL EPISODE chased in the five path, was driven in the four path around the turn and under left handed urging while floating out to the six path into the stretch, but flattened. TWIRLING GRACE brushed with an outer foe at the start, trailed in the two path and was no factor around the four path in the stretch. ALICE HARPER brushed with an inner foe at the start, prompted the pace in the three path, was ridden between foes around the turn, had to steady around the five sixteenths pole, and never threatened. VALIANT MISS set the pace in the two path but gaveway along the inside turning into the lane. OBJECTIONS LODGED BY THE RIDERS OF ALICE HARPER, AND FINAL EPISODE ALLEDGING INTERFERENCE ROUNDING THE TURN WERE DISALLOWED.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HARUKI broke in and bumped an inner foe, trailed in the three path and was cued from the four path into the turn, was under a ride while angling out turning into the lane, rallied down the center and got up on the wire to win. FREE SMOKE tracked in the four path, was coaxed from the three path midway around the turn, swung out to the seven path into the stretch, and ran on under steady urging for place. GRIMES prompted the leading duo in the five path, fanned out to the nine path into the lane, and kept on for show. MR. RHODIUM vied for the lead in the two path, headed an inner foe rounding the turn, was floated out to the six path into the lane, and stayed on but was out-finished in the final sixteenth. ROCKINGHAM JOE stalked in the three path, was roused in the two path around the turn and into the lane, got bumped twice by an inward tipping outer rival, and was outrun late. GET KHOZY got bumped by an outer foe at the start but recovered well to lead along the inside into the turn, was headed and under rousing rounding the turn, floated out to the five path into the lane, tipped inwards under right handed cues and bumped an inner foe twice inside the final furlong while fading. CADDY MAN chased along the inside but was no menace.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 8 1M Turf CR: 80. Maiden Claiming Purse 32000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs. Claiming Price $35,000. (If deemed inadvisable to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the Tapeta Course at One Mile and Seventy Yards) (Rail at 28 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GENTLEMAN GERRY got bumped by an inner foe into the first turn and had to check from the three path midway around that turn, tracked in the three path down the backside, tipped inside and was roused midway around the far turn, remained inside into the lane, tipped out to the four path passing the eighth pole, and drew past the inner pacesetter in the final strides. RIO MOON set the pace in the two path, was coaxed along the inside early around the far turn, opened slightly around the two path in upper stretch, and stayed on under steady urging but was caught in the final strides to place. ROUGH AND ROWDY rated around the three path, was ridden between foes in the two path rounding the far turn, floated out to the five path at the top of the lane, altered course inside of a tiring foe passing the eighth pole, and kept on for show. TIO TONY bumped with an outer foe at the start, trailed around the four path, was cued right handed from the three path rounding the far turn, floated out to the five path into the stretch, and improved between foes. ENSIGN SKIP bumped with an inner foe at the start, stalked around the five path, was under right handed urging in the four path rounding the far turn, tipped out to the six path into the lane, but flattened. MEXICOFFEE prompted the pace in the four path, was coaxed from the three path midway around the far turn, was back out in the four path at the top of the stretch, and yielded in the final furlong. SING DIXIE chased around the five path but was no factor around the seven path in the stretch. DONTONIO raced off the pace in the five path and never threatened from out in the nine path down the lane. MO TOWN BLUES was in tight along the inside and bumped an outer foe into the first turn, continued to race in tight quarters and moved up from the rail to press the outer pacesetter into the backstretch, but gaveway approaching the far turn.
